# HTML Structure

## Document pattern

Single-page layout: topbar → `#mainNav` (+ `#navDrawer` on mobile) → sections → footer. Modal `#quoteModal` and `#mobileCtaBar` sit outside main flow.

**Mobile patterns:** `#navToggle` opens `#navDrawer` (section links + Call/Book). `#mobileCtaBar` is sticky bottom Call + Book (≤767px only). Preserve `closeNavDrawer()` when opening `#quoteModal`.

## Section anchors (preserve when editing nav/footer links)

`#hero`, `#services`, `#testimonials`, `#areas`, `#how`, `#why`, `#about`

Nav and footer already link to these IDs — do not rename without updating all references.

## Class naming

Follow existing BEM-like blocks already in the file:

- Block: `.hero`, `.service-card`, `.review-card`, `.footer-grid`
- Element: `.hero-headline`, `.service-card-body`, `.nav-logo-main`
- Modifier: `.btn-gold`, `.service-pill-gold`, `.nav.elevated`

Do not introduce conflicting utility-class systems.

## Semantic HTML

- One `<h1>` in hero; section titles use `<h2 class="t-lg">`
- Use `<section>` with `id` for major blocks
- Form inside modal: labels paired with inputs; add `name` when wiring backend
- Images: always `alt` text; replace emoji placeholders with `<img src="assets/images/...">`

## Accessibility

- Interactive elements: real `<button>` for actions, `<a href>` for navigation/call/email
- Modal: close on overlay click, Escape key (already implemented)
- Focus styles: preserve `:focus` rules on form inputs
- `tel:` and `mailto:` links for phone and email CTAs

## Copy tone

People-first, direct, local (Bergen County). Avoid corporate jargon. Founder name: **Junior Solice**.
